Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setDefaultWorkspace(25.10)                          setDefaultWorkspace(25.10)

Name
       setDefaultWorkspace - Sets specified workspace as the default

Syntax
       setDefaultWorkspace

       [-help]

       -name <workspaceName>

       [-dir <directory>]

       Sets  specified  workspace  as  the  default.  The default workspace is
       loaded automatically when the software starts. So if you  want  Innovus
       to load a workspace automatically at startup, you need to first save it
       as default.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setDefaultWorkspace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setDefaultWorkspace

       -name <workspaceName>
              Specifies the name of the workspace to be set as default.

       -dir <directory>
              Specifies the location of the workspace to be set as default.

Example
       The  following  example sets the TestWorkspace workspace in the current
       working directory as default.

       setDefaultWorkspace -name TestWorkspace

